      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PLAYA BLANCA (6) was brave in last week's heat when she drew poorly and had to work when racing three wide without cover but boxed on solidly for fifth. Had looked close to a win when placed in her previous four outings, coming from this barrier for a 2m second at Menangle two back. Gets her chance to break through. RAYS REDEMPTION (1) has been coming from wider or second row draws but has still managed to clock in fourth in his last two outings. Each way player aided by the ace draw. PETES CRUNCH TIME (7) should be reaching peak fitness third-up and owns decent records both here and at the distance. Draws for a trail and if he gets the gaps could show his best. ROCKNROLL GIG (8) draws a little lower than he did last week and had been racing consistently prior so respect. DOUBLE IT HARRY (3) will be fitter for recent racing and gets his best draw of the campaign so far.",
